Came on a Saturday morning before heading to the mall. There is street parking in addition to a garage in the same building. I can't speak to foot or vehicle traffic during the work week, but it was very comfortable and relaxed on a Saturday. The space is very open with plenty of seating. Tons of drink and snack options, with some international variety.  I had an everything bagel with cream cheese and it was served hot. Perfect amount of crisp compared to some chains that seem to always burn it when I ask for the bagel toasted. My wife had a breakfast sandwich on a croissant, and liked it.  Very reasonably priced considering the great location. They also have free WiFi!  Things I didn't personally try, but may be of interest to others: deli sandwiches all use Boar's Head meats and cheeses, and coffee is a relatively local brand "Chesapeake Bay Roasting Company"
